name: Free 7 Day Healthy Meal Plan (Sept 23-29)
summary: A free 7-day, flexible weight loss meal plan including breakfast, lunch and dinner ideas and a shopping list. All recipes include macros and Weight Watchers points.

name: Apple Butter

name: Everything You Need to Organize Your Pantry
summary: My secret to healthy cooking starts with a well-organized pantry — because if you can see all the nutritious ingredients you have to cook with, the inspiration for filling and flavorful meals will come much more easily. With the help of a few simple tools and gadgets, you can transform your kitchen pantry in no time. So whether you’re tidying up after the holidays or preparing for an early spring cleaning, I’ve rounded up my favorite food storage and organizing items that will make it easier to enjoy healthy recipes with your family.

It can also help save you money, especially if you get takeout frequently, and ensure less food goes to waste in your kitchen. name: Lemon-Parsley Foil Packet Potatoes
summary: Lemon-Parsley Foil Packet Potatoes can be grilled or baked in the oven! A delicious side dish, and the best part – easy cleanup!

name: Houston’s Veggie Burger
summary: This is a veggie burger that even hearty meat-eaters will love! Made with beans, oats, brown rice, beets and a whole lot of spices, this veggie burger is a real crowd pleaser.

name: Air Fryer Shishito Peppers
summary: Easy Air Fryer Shishito Peppers come out charred and blistered. Finish with a squeeze of lemon over the top and they are delicious!

name: Burma Superstar Chicken Dal Curry
summary: Chicken Dal Curry is a comforting Burmese stew made with yellow peas, chicken, ginger, turmeric, curry and spices.

name: Spicy Tuna Poke Bowl
summary: This Spicy Tuna Poke Bowl is made with chunks of fresh tuna, avocado, cucumbers, spicy mayo and scallions cut on the bias served on a bed of steamed rice – YES please!!

name: Basil Oil
summary: Making basil oil is so simple, trust me you’ll want to drizzle it all over your chicken, fish, tomatoes, vegetables or with some crusty bread!

name: Orecchiette with Sausage and Broccoli Rabe
summary: Orecchiette with Sausage and Broccoli Rabe uses chicken sausage in place of pork sausage and a whole lot of garlic! This lightened up version of my favorite Italian classic pasta dish will not disappoint!!

name: Chicken Zucchini Stir Fry
summary: This quick Chicken and Zucchini Stir Fry is delicious, made with chicken breast, zucchini and an easy stir fry sauce.

name: How To Make Perfect Instant Pot Quinoa
summary: Learn how to make perfect, fluffy Instant Pot quinoa using my foolproof method! This healthy grain is an easy addition to loads of meals, and it’s ready in minutes in the pressure cooker.

name: Lighter Eggplant Parmesan
summary: This Lighter Eggplant Parmesan Recipe is one of my favorite ways to eat eggplant. No breading, no frying, just eggplant, cheese and marinara.

name: Southwestern Black Bean, Quinoa and Mango Salad
summary: Delicious Southwestern Black Bean, Quinoa and Mango Salad is a tasty way to get more vegetables and plant-based foods into your diet.

name: Baked Crab and Corn Cakes
summary: Deliciously Baked Corn and Crab Cakes made with lump crab and sweet summer corn. Bake them in the oven or air fryer!

name: Tzatziki Fish Tacos
summary: Tzatziki Fish Tacos have a Greek twist! Crisp breaded fish fillets served on tortillas topped with tzatziki sauce made with Greek yogurt, cucumbers and fresh herbs.

name: Buffalo Shrimp Lettuce Wraps
summary: These easy, low-carb Buffalo Shrimp Lettuce Wraps are spicy, light and delicious topped with celery and blue cheese or ranch dressing. Ready in under 15 minutes!

name: Air Fryer Chicken Milanese with Baby Arugula
summary: Crisp, golden, delicious Air Fryer Chicken Milanese with Baby Arugula and lemon wedges is one of my favorite dinner recipes!

name: Bruschetta with Tomato and Basil
summary: Bruschetta with Tomato and Basil, one of my favorite ways to use up all my summer tomatoes is with this simple appetizer or side dish.

name: Perfectly Grilled Zucchini Recipe
summary: Make Perfectly Grilled Zucchini all summer long! Quick and easy, great as a side dish with anything you’re grilling.

name: Grilled Vegetable Platter with Yogurt Mint Sauce
summary: This beautiful, Grilled Vegetables Platter with Yogurt Mint Sauce is so colorful and delicious. An easy summer side dish made with asparagus, zucchini, squash, red onion and bell peppers.

name: Zesty Lime Shrimp and Avocado Salad
summary: Zesty Lime Shrimp and Avocado Salad, a light and refreshing salad that requires no cooking! Lime juice and cilantro are the key ingredients to creating this wonderful, healthy salad you’ll want to make all summer long.

name: Breakfast BLT
summary: Breakfast BLT made with center cut bacon, lettuce, tomato and egg on whole wheat bread.

name: Mexican Shrimp Diablo
summary: This delicious Mexican Shrimp dish is made with saucy Chipotle shrimp served over a bed of corn, zucchini, and red onions, and served with a side of avocado.

name: Salmon Avocado Salad
summary: This Salmon Avocado Salad is made with my two favorite super foods – avocado and wild salmon. I could eat this every day!

name: Campfire Dinner Meatloaf Foil Packets
summary: These Campfire Meatloaf Foil Packets are great for camping, glamping or for an easy weeknight dinner made with turkey meatloaf, BBQ sauce and succotash.

name: Chicken Chimichangas
summary: Crispy chicken chimichangas (air fryer or baked) are a healthier twist on the Tex-Mex favorite! They’re filled with cheese, green chiles, and seasoned shredded chicken, then topped with fresh pico de gallo.

name: Chickpea Salad with Cucumbers and Tomatoes
summary: This healthy, summer Chickpea Salad with cucumbers and tomatoes is great for lunch or as a side dish with anything you’re grilling!

name: Air Fryer Chicken Breast
summary: This foolproof recipe for making boneless air fryer chicken breast will give you perfectly juicy chicken every time.

name: Air Fryer Asian-Glazed Boneless Chicken Thighs
summary: These Air Fryer Asian-Glazed Boneless Chicken Thighs come out so juicy and delicious, I’m simply obsessed with this recipe!

name: Taco Stuffed Zucchini Boats
summary: These low-carb stuffed turkey taco zucchini boats are so easy and delicious, a fun twist on taco night!

name: Grilled Cumin Spiced Pork Tenderloin
summary: This easy Grilled Cumin Spiced Pork Tenderloin is perfect for summer nights. I season it with a quick, flavorful rub then throw it on the grill. While it cooks for 30 minutes, I make a salad and dinner is ready!

name: Vegan Caesar Salad
summary: This Vegan Caesar Salad is delicious! The Caesar Salad dressing is made with raw cashews to make it creamy along with lemon juice, Dijon, garlic and capers.

name: Pineapple Shrimp Fried Rice
summary: I love this Malaysian-inspired Pineapple Shrimp Fried Rice, it has a delicious flavor combination of savory, sweet and spicy. Serve it in hollowed out pineapples for a beautiful presentation!

name: Air Fryer Cajun Shrimp Dinner
summary: This fast and easy Air Fryer Cajun Shrimp recipe is a meal-in-one, made with shrimp, sausage, and lots of colorful vegetables such as zucchini, yellow squash and bell peppers.

name: California Grilled Chicken Avocado and Mango Salad
summary: Grilled Chicken pairs beautifully with avocados and mangoes in this delicious salad, perfect for those warmer nights you don’t want to heat up the kitchen.

name: Parmesan-Basil Air Fryer Salmon (or Baked)
summary: I’m obsessed with this Basil-Parmesan Air Fryer Salmon recipe! It comes out perfectly juicy in the air fryer, or bake it in the oven!

name: Potato and Green Bean Salad
summary: This Potato and Green Bean Salad with balsamic vinaigrette is a delicious mayo-free potato salad, perfect for potlucks and a great side dish with anything you’re grilling!

name: Mediterranean Sea Bass
summary: This healthy Mediterranean Sea Bass is smothered in a piquant, healthy, Mediterranean-inspired sauce made from tomatoes, white wine, fennel and olives.

name: Everything Parmesan Crisps
summary: I love making these Everything Parmesan Crisps as a low-carb snack, to add to Caesar salad in place of croutons, with soup, or a great addition to any charcuterie board as an appetizer.

name: Green Detox Soup with Toasted Hemp Gremolata
summary: Delicious Green Detox Soup with Toasted Hemp Gremolata is not your typical detox soup, this one is loaded with healthy fats and hemp seeds, a complete protein so it keeps you full too! Perfect if you need a reset from a weekend spent indulging!

name: Air Fryer Hard Boiled Eggs
summary: Making hard boiled eggs in the air fryer is so quick and easy, no water needed! It’s the only way I cook eggs now!

name: Crispy Avocado Egg Rolls (Air Fryer or Oven)
summary: These easy Air Fryer Avocado Egg Rolls are inspired by the Cheesecake Factory egg rolls, only healthier because they are made in the Air fryer or oven.

name: Smoked Salmon Breakfast Flatbread
summary: These everything bagel flatbreads, which are great for breakfast or breakfast-for-dinner combine two of my favorite foods – lox and everything bagel seasoning!

name: Ranch Chicken Salad
summary: This light and easy chicken salad recipe made with leftover rotisserie chicken breast meat and my homemade ranch dressing. Great for lunch and meal prep!

name: Skinnytaste Air Fryer Cookbook: Get a Free 39-Page Bonus Download with Your Pre-Order
summary: I’m beyond excited that in just a few short weeks my new cookbook The Skinnytaste Air Fryer Cookbook will finally be hitting bookstores May 7, but it’s available to pre-order now!!

name: Key Lime Yogurt Pie
summary: This easy Key Lime Yogurt Pie is a cross between a key lime pie and a key lime cheesecake with a light, creamy filling that is sweet and tart, made with key lime juice, yogurt and cream cheese in a graham cracker crust.

name: Chicken Parmesan Lasagna
summary: This easy Chicken Parmesan Lasagna is a combination of two classic dishes. It’s the perfect family-friendly dish to feed a large crowd!

name: Thin Tortilla Pizza
summary: This easy tortilla pizza recipe is delicious, low-calorie and quick to whip up for lunch. Just add your favorite pizza toppings, ready in under 15 minutes!

name: Tex Mex Migas
summary: Migas is a popular Tex Mex breakfast dish made with chopped corn tortillas, cheese, tomatoes, jalapeños, and onions. I serve it plated with tortillas on the side, but they can also be wrapped in a tortilla, taco style.

name: Chicken and Asparagus Lemon Stir Fry
summary: This quick weeknight Chicken and Asparagus Lemon Stir Fry is perfect for spring, made with lean chicken breast, asparagus, fresh lemon, garlic and ginger.

name: The Best Turkey Meatloaf Recipe
summary: Turkey meatloaf is a favorite in our house! This healthy ground turkey meatloaf recipe is a staple in my home! Easy and delicious.

name: BBQ Chicken Quesadilla
summary: This BBQ Chicken Quesadilla is a fun twist on a traditional quesadilla. Made with chicken breast, BBQ sauce, cheese, red onion and cilantro on a high fiber whole wheat tortilla.

name: Veggie Ham and Cheese Breakfast Egg Casserole
summary: Make this delicious and easy Veggie Ham and Cheese Breakfast Egg Casserole for brunch or make it ahead for meal prep for the week.

name: Honey Lemon Bars with Whole Wheat Shortbread Crust
summary: Pucker Up! These sweet and tangy Honey Lemon Bars made with fresh lemon, lemon zest and honey and a whole wheat shortbread crust are a little lighter than traditional lemon bars, but are so tasty and hard to resist.

name: Freezer Breakfast Burritos
summary: These freezer breakfast burritos, stuffed with scrambled eggs, scallions, bell pepper, bacon and cheese, are a great way to start the day! Make them ahead and freeze them for meal prep so you can have them ready any day of the week.

name: Heather’s Buddha Bowl
summary: This easy Buddha Bowl is made with roasted broccoli, butternut squash, and onions piled on top of whole grain rice and topped with sliced avocado, a sunny-side fried egg, and crunchy pecans.

name: Hard Boiled Eggs
summary: If you want to know how to hard boil eggs, this foolproof stove top method has you covered. It makes perfect hard boiled eggs every time!

name: Swiss Chard Eggs Benedict
summary: I love this lighter take on Eggs Benedict made with Canadian bacon, Swiss chard and poached eggs on a whole wheat English muffin. Perfect for breakfast or brunch!

name: Apricot-Rum Glazed Spiral Ham
summary: Apricot-Rum Glazed Spiral Ham is perfect for the Holidays, and easy since the ham is already cooked you’re basically just heating it up and adding your own glaze.

name: Green Bean Salad
summary: One of my favorite ways to enjoy green beans–in a chilled green bean salad! The delicious flavors of these balsamic green beans made with black olives, scallions and eggs complement any meal or holiday potluck.

name: Yogurt Waffles
summary: Whip up these protein-packed yogurt waffles for breakfast & freeze the rest for easy meal prep! A simple recipe that makes fluffy waffles you’ll love.

name: Sesame Crusted Tuna Steak on Arugula
summary: Sesame Crusted Tuna Steak on Arugula drizzled with a balsamic soy-ginger vinaigrette –all I can say is yum! This is an easy main course salad or appetizer.

name: White Bean Turkey Chili
summary: A delicious, creamy White Bean Turkey Chili recipe made with canned white beans, ground turkey, aromatics and spices – no tomatoes!

name: Shrimp Scampi with Broccoli Orzo
summary: This quick and easy Shrimp Scampi with Broccoli Orzo is a dish the whole family will love and it’s ready in under 30 minutes!

name: Slow Cooker Split Pea Soup
summary: Making Split Pea Soup in the Slow Cooker is so easy and perfect for busy weeknight meals. It’s also freezer friendly, so you can make a batch and freeze the leftovers for another night.

name: Broccoli and Cheese Stuffed Chicken (Oven or Air Fryer)
summary: Broccoli and Cheese Stuffed Chicken breasts are filled with cheddar and broccoli, then rolled up, breaded and baked in the oven or air fryer!

name: Seattle Smoked Salmon Chowder
summary: This creamy Smoked Salmon Chowder is truly comfort food in a bowl! Made with hot-smoked salmon (full of heart-healthy fats) and a ton of nutrient-packed veggies (onion, celery, carrots, potatoes, corn and cauliflower), it’s a good-for-you soup the whole family will love. Stove top and Instant Pot directions provided.

name: Instant Pot Corned Beef and Cabbage
summary: This easy Instant Pot Corned Beef and Cabbage recipe comes out perfectly tender every time! Made with corned beef brisket, cabbage, and carrots, it’s the perfect St. Patrick’s Day dinner.

name: Cream of Broccoli Soup
summary: Cream of Broccoli Soup is a favorite of comfort food mine. This healthy version uses no cream, simple ingredients and can be made in under 30 minutes!

name: Cilantro-Lime Fish Tacos
summary: These easy Cilantro Lime Fish Tacos are made with flaky white fish, tomatoes, jalapeños, cilantro and lime topped with avocado.

name: Kale and Potato Soup with Turkey Sausage
summary: Kale and Potato Soup with Turkey Sausage is an easy, hearty soup made with kale, potatoes, carrots and turkey or chicken sausage.

name: Banana Foster Crepes
summary: Banana Foster Crepes combine two of my favorite desserts – homemade crepes and bananas fosters! This slimmed down make-over is delicious and perfect anytime you’re craving something sweet!

name: Instant Pot Chicken Taco Chili
summary: This Instant Pot Chicken Chili is made with chicken, beans, corn, tomatoes, and taco seasoning for a hearty, flavorful, and healthy dinner. This easy taco chili comes together in just over 30 minutes, perfect for busy weeknights!

name: Honey Garlic Shrimp
summary: For a quick and easy weeknight stir-fry, you will love this easy Asian Honey Garlic Shrimp recipe! It’s sweet, spicy, savory, and so good!!

name: Crustless Broccoli Cheddar Quiche
summary: Broccoli and cheese is one of my favorite quiche combinations! This low-carb Crustless Broccoli Cheddar Quiche is light and delicious, perfect for breakfast or brunch (or even a light dinner)!
